content.description:
A very very nice dihedral, not very large. A really nice climb! The top is not significant, but the part before is really worth it.

At the very left of the main cliff, a but hidden in the woods. On the right of the route, you can see a less perfect dihedral, and a fixed rope.
size 1 and under. Very small nuts and cams for the dihedral crack. Some regular pieces for the top.

The obvious black streak. Climb up an easier slab with some tricky moves leading to the underclings at the break. Shake off a little and get ready for hard moves straight to the top with very little places to rest, Going from big thuggy moves to techy sidepulling. Stay straight up in the bolt line at the end for a full value line.



The black streak to the right of Zephyr. Be sure to check the tides before going to the cliff! 

7 bolts plus anchor
Very nice cliff, sunny, on the waterline. You have to check the tides! If it's high tide, you just can't access the place. A lot of trad and some bolted lines too. 5.8 to 5.12a.
